name: 3. Exploratory Data Analysis
content:
EDA on Policies and Claims :

  • Objective: Perform exploratory data analysis on the combined data.
  • Process: Generate visualizations and statistics to understand trends, patterns, and relationships between variables like claim amounts, policy tenure, driver demographics, etc.
  • Output: Insights and trends that guide feature computation and model selection.


Cluster Profiling on Claims Data

  • Objective: Segment the claims data into clusters to identify distinct groups with similar characteristics.
  • Process: Apply clustering algorithms (e.g., K-means) to group claims based on common features like claim amount, incident type, and customer demographics.
  • Output: Cluster profiles that can be used for risk assessment and customer segmentation.


EDA Timeseries Analysis

  • Objective: Analyze the trends in claims over time.
  • Process: Use time-series analysis techniques to identify seasonality, trends, and outliers in the frequency and severity of claims.
  • Output: Time-series insights to guide forecasting and prediction efforts.
